{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F01-v112-terminal-failure-scope","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The retained v1.12 terminal diagnosis is confined to non-performance schema and custody evidence: formal-binding v9 rejected a required zero-byte stderr identity because fileDigest required at least one byte, and v1.13 neither resumes nor reuses a v1.12 formal outcome."},{"id":"F02-formal-binding-v10-digest-split","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Formal-binding v10 keeps fileDigest.bytes minimum 1 exclusively for implementation files and uses streamFileDigest.bytes minimum 0 exclusively for exactly 20 preformal log identities; realistic empty stderr rows validate while negative streams and zero-byte implementation sources are rejected."},{"id":"F03-exact-preclaim-before-attempt","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"binding_main derives the actual preformal_log_rows, verifies the root schema references and exact byte minima, and validates the 20 rows before _Captures or _Attempt can create a binding claim; create_formal_binding repeats the compatibility check."},{"id":"F04-full-root-validation-before-publication","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"create_formal_binding validates the complete assembled object against the exact meta-validated Draft 2020-12 root schema before creating its output directory or publishing any binding sidecar or formal-binding.json, while the independent strict verifier and formal-input preflight remain mandatory."},{"id":"F05-fresh-seed-and-prior-domain-arithmetic","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The SHA-256 derivation yields 10 unique current masters and 1,360 unique current streams; the exposed v1.0-v1.12 universe yields 120 unique masters and 16,320 unique streams, with zero internal or cross-domain overlap in all master/stream classes in both verifier implementations."},{"id":"F06-scientific-continuity","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"All 17 sealed scientific protocol blocks remain byte-semantically equal to v1.12 and retain canonical SHA-256 fa44fd93a672db3905d45a0e99c568985e7e2e5d02d32043c830db413005a5c3; the four sealed scientific kernel source digests are unchanged and raw-result representation remains v9."},{"id":"F07-same-wheel-unequal-environments","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The fresh QA and runtime environments contain the same non-editable Prospect distribution digest, the 45-row runtime inventory exactly matches requirements-wm001.lock, QA contains pytest/ruff/mypy, and the runtime contains none of those QA-only distributions; IEEE precision gates pass on the bound CUDA runtime."},{"id":"F08-command10-exact-zero-stderr","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The runbook captures command 10 stdout and stderr separately and retires the version on nonzero exit or any stderr byte; preformal and independent audit consumers require bytes 0 with SHA-256 of the empty stream, and adversarial tests reject nonempty stderr and mutated identity receipts."},{"id":"F09-explicit-assurance-boundary","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"Protocol, schema, seal, binding, operator, audit, and adjudication identities consistently bind trust model prospect.wm001.trust-model.v1 with tamper_resistant and external_attestation false; cooperative exclusive path use is explicit and is not overstated as hostile-writer resistance."},{"id":"F10-one-shot-lifecycle-and-custody","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Fresh v1.13 paths are absent prospectively, version-scoped claims and hidden staging paths are no-replace, outer completions bind terminal inodes, and the runbook preserves the sole development, audit, closure, preformal, binding, formal, formal-audit, and adjudication sequence without same-version retry."},{"id":"F11-adversarial-test-coverage","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Coverage directly exercises the schema-definition split, realistic 20-row empty-stderr manifest, negative and zero-source rejection, wrong empty-stream digest rejection, exact preclaim ordering, full generated root validation, and no-publication behavior on full-schema failure; focused tests, Ruff, and both mypy gates pass."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1638,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"f58fc657669d4bb257fefdc515df8d23e83abeacc2149762bd3d78eeb9e9d6ed"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistemic/maturity.py","sha256":"2a81abe60f12285f66f2bcd351589de28851412f1d9df7f2003843a845a2510e"},{"bytes":13611,"path":"bench/epistemic/problem.py","sha256":"c66ae13d3e833ffd1be1562a89e0e9035d6197b95723179b930c1ca2a1059c66"},{"bytes":1097,"path":"bench/epistemic/run_maturity.py","sha256":"86ae2c3175262f559a274827c96c30212fbdb9250e3a4614f92c861b7498feb7"},{"bytes":20656,"path":"bench/epistemic/runtime_lane.py","sha256":"d8f0c7a85be786c3a813ee1f169abcbc2791a642e46fba5978f7a1140cc50387"},{"bytes":278,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/SEALED_PROTOCOL.sha256","sha256":"c53b60f5a2c5d3ac552e473094bac89598516a92b3876273dac660876808d70e"},{"bytes":75,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/__init__.py","sha256":"0390d290ffee36c3e2a696938bab498fddba3991f970676e20a0cfe0d77dba83"},{"bytes":173718,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/adjudication.py","sha256":"286d91dde356d363ada8b78a3dd0ccab07a2e06c9b69503cbce19db7f54e10f9"},{"bytes":102887,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/analysis.py","sha256":"4e0839b7496a1a8b8a96ec7bcf2975f1713654f159da0eaa1a7c04914fade93a"},{"bytes":45307,"path":"bench/world_mod